cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with decidability of problems related to integer matrix multiplication, which involves computational complexity and algorithms (cs.CC). The problems involve sets of matrices and their closure under matrix multiplication, which relates to discrete structures (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.LO). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) to prove the undecidability results.
